    "body": "So there are two ways to go about this. \r\n\r\n1. Simply rename the files, locally. This solves (?) your problem. \r\n2. An idea I've had for a couple of years, but never got around to fixing. Having an additional meta-data storage, so you can attach metadata to wallets. These would be 'stub' files, which e..g contains a user-friendly name, but also, in the case of hardware wallets, can say things like \"at derivation path xx/yy/zz, the key `myTestSigner` resides\". \r\n\r\nThe latter thing is quite a big project, and not something that we've prioritized. Our preferred wallet solution, `clef` still lacks a UI and afaik is not widely adopted, so I'm a bit hesitant to spend a lot of time on it until we have a better UI/UX. ",
